100 Years Ago Today, This is What Was Happening ...

On February 1, 1926, the United States Senate continued to debate the proposed immigration restrictions aimed at limiting the influx of Southern and Eastern Europeans. In Europe, a severe economic crisis gripped Germany, raising fears of hyperinflation and political instability. Meanwhile, in the realm of culture, the film industry buzzed with excitement over the release of new talkies, marking a significant shift in cinema.
